sub

Class SubscriptionParam

  • java.lang.Object
    • sub.SubscriptionParam

  • public class SubscriptionParam
extends Object
    Used to define the parameters of a subscription to the SubscriptionService.

    type can take take any String value, but currently Subscribable data types are:

    • StockRecord
    • FilterRecord
    • AccountActivity
    • HeartBeat
    • MessageGlob

    The HashMap<String,String> regexes maps the different fields of a Subscribable object to a specified regular expression. Each regex follows the standard Java regular expression guidelines.

    The HashMap<String,String> equations maps the different numeric fields of a Subscribable object to a specified equation. Each expression in the equation uses JavaScript arithmetic operators. See equations.

    Example type, field,regex pairs, and field,equation pairs:

     type = "StockRecord"; {"symbol","GOOG|AAPL|MSFT"};                      // subscribes to all StockRecords for GOOG, AAPL, and MSFT
 type = "StockRecord"; {"symbol","AMZN"},{"source","SimApiSession0"};    // subscribes to all StockRecords for AMZN from simulator with simID SimulationParam
 type = "FilterRecord"; {"symbol","Chaikin.*"};                          // subscribes to all FilterRecords from "Chaikin Money Flow" and "Chaikin Oscillator"
 type = "HeartBeat"; {"source","SimApiSession0"};{"time","0 = x % 60000  // subscribes to HeartBeats from "SimApiSessio0" every minute
    Author:
    Kyle
    See Also:
    SubscriptionService, Subscribable

      • equations

        public HashMap<String,String> equations
        A map of field names to accepted equations.

        Valid for numeric field values only. Numbers will be processed as long.

        Equations are of the form: 

         100 < x
 0 = x % 60000
 (Double) (<|>|=|>=|<=) (algebraic expression using x)
        Where x will be the value of the equations.key field of the Subscribable record.
        The algebraic expression must only use x. It supports all JavaScript arithmetic operators.
        See Also:
        JavaScript Operators

      • match

        public boolean match(Subscribable record)
        Tells whether or not this SubscriptionParam wants the Subscribable object.

        Compares the various fields of the Subscribable object with the regexes listed in this SubscriptionParam. Uses standard Java regular expressions.

        Compares the various fields of the Subscribable object with the equations listed in this SubscriptionParam. Uses standard JavaScript operators and expressions.

        Parameters:
        record - a Subscribable object that is checked
        Returns:
        true if, and only if, this record matches all the regex in the SubscriptionParam
